description:
Make an HTTP request to fetch a URL. Returns formatted response: 'HTTP {code} {status}

=== Headers ===
{headers}

=== Body ===
{body}'. For large responses exceeding the threshold (~100KB), the body is saved to a .ide/fetch_*.txt file instead — read that file with read_file to get the full content. Supports file download (save_as), multipart form upload (form/form_files), custom headers/cookies, timeout control, redirect following, and encoding conversion. Example: {"url": "https://api.example.com/data", "method": "GET"}
